WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Hitokakera no yuuki hirogete
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:53.430
Saisho wa minna BARABARA ni egaite ita chiheisen

10
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

11
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

12
00:00:53.740 --> 00:01:00.440
Ima nara hitotsu no bouenkyou de nozokeru

13
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

14
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

15
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:09.980
Kimi no KOKORO madowasu unmei no shoppai KONPASU

16
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

17
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Sakate ni kaji toru yo
Set a new course, turn the tables now

18
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! SHIGARAMI mo kako mo sutete
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

19
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Bokura nara sore demo waraeteru hazu
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

20
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

21
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:34.900
Yume wo kanaeru tame no namida naraba

22
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

23
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
Oshiku wa nai PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

24
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

25
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:53.130
Concerto

26
00:02:03.350 --> 00:02:05.230
Just a little more...

27
00:02:05.230 --> 00:02:10.360
Everyone will be so impressed
if I find the gold first!

28
00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:18.700
Ruins up here, too...

29
00:02:24.790 --> 00:02:25.750
Ow!

30
00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:27.960
What's with this place?!

31
00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:30.000
The ground is slanted...

32
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:31.880
I'll go around that way.

33
00:02:38.050 --> 00:02:40.310
Gold! Gold!

34
00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:43.890
Stay.

35
00:02:43.890 --> 00:02:45.600
Stay, Holy.

36
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:47.360
Holy, stay.

37
00:02:57.070 --> 00:02:59.700
I got too cocky!

38
00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:01.740
I should've just gone back!

39
00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:03.960
I'm gonna die...!

40
00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:10.880
You're the third one
to make it here today...

41
00:03:11.250 --> 00:03:12.210
Huh?

42
00:03:12.210 --> 00:03:13.170
Who are you?!

43
00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:16.840
That spider-head is so careless!

44
00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:20.100
You must've beaten Gedatsu.

45
00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:23.770
He must mean that guy from earlier!

46
00:03:25.060 --> 00:03:27.270
Oh, don't worry.

47
00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:30.190
The world is a better place
without an imbecile like him.

48
00:03:30.190 --> 00:03:31.520
Wouldn't you agree?

49
00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:44.950
Huh? I tripped over–

50
00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:53.630
Don't be scared.

51
00:03:53.630 --> 00:03:55.970
That's my pet dog Holy.

52
00:03:55.970 --> 00:03:57.590
He won't bite.

53
00:03:57.970 --> 00:04:01.390
B-But...! This guy is just
lying here, torn to shreds!

54
00:04:01.390 --> 00:04:06.100
Holy is well trained, 
so he won't bite anyone on a whim.

55
00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:10.560
I'm the one who cut him up.

56
00:04:11.690 --> 00:04:14.110
That's even scarier! Who are you?!

57
00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:15.900
Who are you?

58
00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:17.150
My name is Ohm.

59
00:04:17.150 --> 00:04:19.070
You're scary!

60
00:04:17.780 --> 00:04:19.070
Just be silent!

61
00:04:19.070 --> 00:04:20.320
He's too scary!

62
00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:23.700
I am lamenting the frailty of man.

63
00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:22.490
I don't like him!

64
00:04:23.700 --> 00:04:24.580
Huh?

65
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:29.040
Why do humans fight and die in vain,

66
00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:31.790
despite knowing 
the transience of life?!

67
00:04:32.670 --> 00:04:34.000
What the...?

68
00:04:34.730 --> 00:04:36.840
From the day they are born,

69
00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:38.430
they spend their lives 
pursuing happiness...

70
00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:40.470
only to die fighting!

71
00:04:41.180 --> 00:04:44.970
It would have been better if
they never did anything at all...

72
00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:47.350
Such is the fate of humanity...

73
00:04:47.350 --> 00:04:48.680
Truly a tragedy...

74
00:04:49.730 --> 00:04:52.770
However, there is
one path to salvation!

75
00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:55.980
Everyone must die!

76
00:04:56.730 --> 00:04:59.030
Why's he saying such scary stuff?!

77
00:04:59.030 --> 00:05:00.610
This is crazy...!

78
00:05:01.240 --> 00:05:03.780
What have you come here for?

79
00:05:03.780 --> 00:05:06.040
Oh, I'm just looking for gol–

80
00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:08.410
Greed begets strife.

81
00:05:08.410 --> 00:05:09.120
Huh?

82
00:05:09.500 --> 00:05:11.120
Allow me to save you.

83
00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:14.090
You're going to save... me?

84
00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:22.090
Your earthly desires shall
vanish upon your death.

85
00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:26.680
He doesn't plan to save me at all!

86
00:05:36.730 --> 00:05:37.820
Kamakiri...!

87
00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:40.320
Kamakiri!

88
00:05:42.450 --> 00:05:43.570
Go...

89
00:05:44.410 --> 00:05:46.120
Go, Raki...

90
00:05:46.780 --> 00:05:48.370
But, Kamakiri...!

91
00:05:50.580 --> 00:05:55.460
Wyper... is headed...
for God's Shrine...

92
00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:58.250
But Enel... isn't there!

93
00:05:58.250 --> 00:06:00.510
You can still stop him...

94
00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:03.260
Stop Wyper...

95
00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:06.850
All right! I got it, so save your breath!

96
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:14.350
No one... can beat him...!

97
00:06:14.480 --> 00:06:17.820
I am lightning.

98
00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:27.120
He's... invincible...

99
00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:36.500
He is pure lightning... a divine force
that has been feared for millennia...

100
00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:41.170
I'll stop Wyper!

101
00:06:41.170 --> 00:06:42.630
Wait here.

102
00:06:42.630 --> 00:06:46.220
I'm going to leave Aisa's bag with you!

103
00:06:57.860 --> 00:07:00.520
No one... can beat him...!

104
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:03.520
He's... invincible...

105
00:07:03.520 --> 00:07:07.910
Kamakiri is so strong...
yet his will has been broken!

106
00:07:09.740 --> 00:07:11.190
The Thunder-Thunder Fruit...

107
00:07:11.190 --> 00:07:16.000
To think that Enel ate a logia devil fruit,
the most powerful kind of all...!

108
00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:17.540
I have to stop Wyper quickly!

109
00:07:23.340 --> 00:07:27.720
I think I recognize
this place... Or not...

110
00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:28.890
No, I do...

111
00:07:30.100 --> 00:07:32.100
Or not...

112
00:07:32.100 --> 00:07:33.100
No, I do.

113
00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:35.890
Does it just look similar?

114
00:07:40.860 --> 00:07:42.570
Did you just laugh at me?!

115
00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:49.870
What? You're the one who
tagged along just to get food.

116
00:07:49.870 --> 00:07:53.290
That's what you get for
sticking around. Get lost!

117
00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:02.040
Hey, dumbass!

118
00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:03.170
Whoa, whoa!

119
00:08:04.550 --> 00:08:07.170
Wait! There's no more food in there!

120
00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:08.680
Let go! Hey!

121
00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:12.390
Where are you flying off to?!

122
00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:16.270
This is a crazy place I wound up in!

123
00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:21.400
A dead end?!

124
00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:28.570
You can't be serious...
I walked all this way!

125
00:08:29.450 --> 00:08:30.320
Wait...

126
00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:32.830
Could it be a trick door?

127
00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:35.870
I got it!

128
00:08:35.870 --> 00:08:39.670
I bet I can get through if I
just punch it hard enough!

129
00:08:39.670 --> 00:08:44.800
Gum-Gum Bazooka!

130
00:08:48.920 --> 00:08:49.930
Huh?

131
00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:51.720
It didn't even budge...

132
00:08:59.350 --> 00:09:01.850
What's going on?!

133
00:09:19.750 --> 00:09:21.790
He's not following me... Phew...

134
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:27.630
Is he a priest too?

135
00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:30.050
There are lots of places to hide here.

136
00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:33.890
I just need to escape and meet up
with Luffy and the others!

137
00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:38.770
He seemed like a swordsman,

138
00:09:38.770 --> 00:09:41.890
so if I stay hidden and keep
my distance, I can escape!

139
00:09:44.980 --> 00:09:46.820
He's run quite a long way.

140
00:09:47.530 --> 00:09:50.570
How foolish, running from salvation.

141
00:09:50.570 --> 00:09:54.320
That in itself is an attachment to life, an earthly desire.

142
00:09:55.830 --> 00:09:56.830
However...!

143
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:18.350
There are no means to survive
on the sad path to attaining peace...

144
00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:24.230
This is the Ordeal of Iron,
with a survival rate of 0%!

145
00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:25.770
Aisa?

146
00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:28.520
I can't just sit here!
I'm going to find Raki!

147
00:10:28.520 --> 00:10:30.030
Hold it!

148
00:10:30.570 --> 00:10:32.320
Stop! Don't!

149
00:10:33.110 --> 00:10:34.240
What a pain...!

150
00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:39.160
I said stop!

151
00:10:39.160 --> 00:10:43.290
What's your problem?!
Let go! Let go of me! Let go!

152
00:10:43.790 --> 00:10:45.750
This has nothing to do with you!

153
00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:50.630
Maybe not, but I can't just
let a kid run off and die!

154
00:10:50.630 --> 00:10:51.880
I'm a warrior!

155
00:10:52.260 --> 00:10:55.550
Yeah, yeah, alright. Little warrior.

156
00:10:56.340 --> 00:10:58.720
Your glares don't scare me.

157
00:10:58.720 --> 00:11:01.180
Um, are you all right?

158
00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:02.390
Just fine!

159
00:11:02.390 --> 00:11:05.060
Come on, quit struggling! Let's go!

160
00:11:05.690 --> 00:11:10.440
No! Let go! I'm gonna
save everyone! Let go!

161
00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:12.860
Knock it off or I'll slug you!

162
00:11:14.070 --> 00:11:15.110
And no crying!

163
00:11:15.780 --> 00:11:19.120
Even two people from
our crew were beaten!

164
00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:21.200
I can't just let you go alone!

165
00:11:21.540 --> 00:11:23.370
Now, hurry and get on.

166
00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:41.510
No way!

167
00:11:47.390 --> 00:11:50.520
Whoa, that scared me!

168
00:11:50.520 --> 00:11:52.230
What's with this cave?!

169
00:11:52.900 --> 00:11:56.740
First there's an earthquake,
then a flood of sea clouds...

170
00:11:58.070 --> 00:11:59.870
I almost drowned there!

171
00:11:59.870 --> 00:12:00.870
Stupid thing!

172
00:12:00.870 --> 00:12:02.700
Open up!

173
00:12:07.370 --> 00:12:09.250
Why is it so huge?!

174
00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:10.670
Damn you!

175
00:12:10.670 --> 00:12:12.670
Where's the exit?!

176
00:12:12.670 --> 00:12:17.380
Gum-Gum Gatling!

177
00:12:27.940 --> 00:12:29.140
Nami!

178
00:12:29.140 --> 00:12:31.150
That leads into the forest!

179
00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:34.860
Nami!

180
00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:37.950
What do we do?

181
00:12:37.950 --> 00:12:39.570
They went into the forest...

182
00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:46.870
Damn it!

183
00:12:48.750 --> 00:12:49.790
You're tough!

184
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:05.560
Whaat's that?!

185
00:13:08.640 --> 00:13:09.480
Who is that?!

186
00:13:09.480 --> 00:13:11.230
Wait... something's coming!

187
00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:18.820
Shoo! Go that way!

188
00:13:20.820 --> 00:13:22.240
It's the Maaster of the Sky!

189
00:13:22.610 --> 00:13:24.450
Was that... Aisa?!

190
00:13:44.720 --> 00:13:46.850
We're...

191
00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:48.310
inside the forest...!

192
00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:55.310
Hey! Put me down!

193
00:13:55.310 --> 00:13:57.440
Are you listening to me?!

194
00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:02.910
You stupid bird!
I oughta chop you up!

195
00:14:09.620 --> 00:14:10.250
Huh?

196
00:14:15.920 --> 00:14:17.750
Th-The giant snake!

197
00:14:17.750 --> 00:14:21.130
Hey, fly higher!
We're gonna get eaten!

198
00:14:23.510 --> 00:14:25.470
Hurry it up! Hey!

199
00:14:27.970 --> 00:14:31.390
It's still coming after us!
That snake seems pissed!

200
00:14:50.330 --> 00:14:52.330
Why, you...!

201
00:15:08.640 --> 00:15:12.980
God's Shrine is at
the top of Giant Jack!

202
00:15:13.600 --> 00:15:16.230
That's where I'll find Enel.

203
00:15:16.230 --> 00:15:22.070
I'm gonna take him down and bring
an end to this 400-year struggle!

204
00:15:23.320 --> 00:15:24.240
Here he comes.

205
00:15:38.330 --> 00:15:43.460
Wyper... Climb that vine any farther
and you'll reach God's Shrine.

206
00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:46.220
Who gave you permission to pass?

207
00:15:47.890 --> 00:15:49.220
Ohm!

208
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:55.390
There is no longer any point
in heading for God's Shrine.

209
00:15:56.270 --> 00:15:57.640
Gan Fall!

210
00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:02.940
What are you doing here?!

211
00:16:03.360 --> 00:16:06.200
Still attached to the position of god?!

212
00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:10.410
No, but I've yet to finish
taking responsibility.

213
00:16:11.160 --> 00:16:16.330
I've just come from
God's Shrine up above.

214
00:16:20.290 --> 00:16:23.300
It was tragic. The shrine
was completely obliterated...

215
00:16:30.930 --> 00:16:34.600
Naturally, Enel was
nowhere to be found.

216
00:16:35.390 --> 00:16:40.350
Perhaps that means he
no longer has any use for it...

217
00:16:42.550 --> 00:16:48.450
It seems their six years
of diligent service is nearing its end.

218
00:16:48.450 --> 00:16:52.180
I thought it fitting to bid you farewell.

219
00:16:56.790 --> 00:17:00.620
Just what is it
you people seek, Ohm?!

220
00:17:01.210 --> 00:17:05.210
Did you say that Enel
isn't in God's Shrine?!

221
00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:24.770
One of Straw Hat's comrades?

222
00:17:24.790 --> 00:17:26.780
Ah, that hurt...!

223
00:17:26.780 --> 00:17:28.530
That bird's gonna pay!

224
00:17:28.530 --> 00:17:29.650
It's you!

225
00:17:33.370 --> 00:17:34.450
Where am I?

226
00:17:39.660 --> 00:17:41.830
Ruins, huh?

227
00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:47.920
Looks like we got us
some feisty ones here...

228
00:17:48.510 --> 00:17:50.630
Hey, hand over the gold!

229
00:17:50.630 --> 00:17:52.630
Oh, my. How tragic.

230
00:17:52.630 --> 00:17:56.640
No one can escape from
my Ordeal of Iron.

231
00:17:56.640 --> 00:18:00.390
If you're going to get in my way,
I'll wipe you all out!

232
00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:05.150
Tell me where Enel
and the Holy Host are!

233
00:18:08.780 --> 00:18:11.950
What's going on with this cave?!

234
00:18:22.830 --> 00:18:27.210
Well, I'm sure you gentlemen
have all sorts of things to say,

235
00:18:27.210 --> 00:18:29.210
but if you wish to be heard,

236
00:18:29.210 --> 00:18:32.170
you'll need to survive here first!

237
00:18:39.810 --> 00:18:41.100
Let's go, Holy.

238
00:18:41.100 --> 00:18:42.850
Go as wild as you want.

239
00:18:44.520 --> 00:18:46.900
That man is our target, Pierre.

240
00:18:46.900 --> 00:18:50.280
We have to stop Enel's priest first!

241
00:18:54.950 --> 00:19:00.410
I can't believe that giant snake
made it all the way up here...

242
00:19:05.170 --> 00:19:06.790
Dammit!

243
00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:11.300
I can't break through. It just
keeps going topsy-turvy!

244
00:19:13.340 --> 00:19:15.550
This cave is messed up!

245
00:19:19.140 --> 00:19:21.350
You can all...

246
00:19:22.770 --> 00:19:24.270
die together!

247
00:19:37.780 --> 00:19:39.990
That's one pesky weapon...!

248
00:19:39.990 --> 00:19:42.540
You Blue Sea people
don't know anything!

249
00:19:43.160 --> 00:19:48.290
The sky has nothing
for outsiders like you!

250
00:19:48.290 --> 00:19:52.630
I'm not about to waste my time
figuring out your problems.

251
00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:57.930
This whole sky thing has
nothing to do with us anyway!

252
00:19:58.590 --> 00:19:59.640
Thought so!

253
00:20:03.350 --> 00:20:06.560
I was planning to take you out
anyway! Works for me!

254
00:20:06.560 --> 00:20:07.520
Die!

255
00:20:14.650 --> 00:20:17.110
This guy's tougher than I thought.

256
00:20:29.290 --> 00:20:30.630
Die, already!

257
00:20:48.890 --> 00:20:50.650
That's right...

258
00:20:50.650 --> 00:20:53.110
It's got poisonous fangs!

259
00:20:59.280 --> 00:21:00.530
This one's got fangs, too!

260
00:21:05.450 --> 00:21:07.750
What's with this dog's moves?!

261
00:21:09.080 --> 00:21:11.580
His name is Holy.

262
00:21:11.580 --> 00:21:14.340
I'm warning you.
I'm a rancher in the sky.

263
00:21:14.340 --> 00:21:16.510
In other words, a sky breeder!

264
00:21:17.090 --> 00:21:20.340
My animals receive training
far beyond ordinary methods.

265
00:21:20.340 --> 00:21:25.350
I trained him to walk on two legs
and even in hand-to-hand combat.

266
00:21:26.100 --> 00:21:27.600
Savor his attacks!

267
00:21:29.680 --> 00:21:31.310
Isn't that a little too far?

268
00:21:39.490 --> 00:21:40.780
Gan Fall...

269
00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:44.740
Even Shura managed to beat you.
Haven't you learned your lesson?

270
00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:48.830
You probably can't even lift
that spear anymore, can you?

271
00:21:48.830 --> 00:21:50.080
You old fool!

272
00:21:50.660 --> 00:21:52.580
Even so, I cannot withdraw!

273
00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:56.290
I still don't know what
you're planning to do!

274
00:21:59.090 --> 00:22:00.920
Don't be conceited!

275
00:22:01.550 --> 00:22:05.850
Even if you knew, someone
like you wouldn't be able...

276
00:22:06.350 --> 00:22:08.470
to understand God's noble ideals!

277
00:22:15.900 --> 00:22:17.690
Aafter them!

278
00:22:17.690 --> 00:22:19.780
After the Shaandians!

279
00:22:23.910 --> 00:22:26.030
What the heck? What was that?!

280
00:22:26.030 --> 00:22:27.280
I heard a "maa"!

281
00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:28.160
Goats?

282
00:22:28.160 --> 00:22:31.200
They're warrior monks!
If we get caught, we'll be killed!

283
00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:33.250
What do you mean "warrior monks"?!

284
00:22:33.250 --> 00:22:34.830
They're Enel's goons!

285
00:22:34.830 --> 00:22:36.420
Hurry up and get out of here!

286
00:22:36.420 --> 00:22:38.920
H-Hold on just a minute!

287
00:22:38.920 --> 00:22:41.510
Where exactly are we headed?!

288
00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:58.690
That damn snake!
It keeps getting in my way!

289
00:23:10.040 --> 00:23:11.830
Hey, Chopper...

290
00:23:12.290 --> 00:23:14.500
Hey! What happened?!

291
00:23:16.330 --> 00:23:17.580
I see...

292
00:23:17.580 --> 00:23:19.840
He was part of the Blue Sea group.

293
00:23:21.590 --> 00:23:24.050
Hey, watch your step over there.

294
00:23:31.770 --> 00:23:32.890
What was that?!

295
00:23:34.430 --> 00:23:36.270
Barbed wire?!

296
00:23:37.900 --> 00:23:40.110
So that's the "ordeal"...

297
00:23:40.690 --> 00:23:41.690
Chopper!

298
00:23:41.690 --> 00:23:43.280
Hey, Chopper!

299
00:23:43.280 --> 00:23:44.780
Say something!

300
00:23:44.780 --> 00:23:47.610
Why did you come here
all by yourself?!

301
00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:49.070
Hey!

302
00:23:49.070 --> 00:23:50.870
Such a shame...

303
00:23:54.540 --> 00:23:56.790
They're made of iron cloud.

304
00:23:57.750 --> 00:24:01.290
Light as a cloud and as hard as iron...

305
00:24:01.290 --> 00:24:04.380
They're blown into shape
by a milky dial.

306
00:24:04.380 --> 00:24:07.050
Each one connects
to an area of the ground.

307
00:24:07.050 --> 00:24:08.800
If you step on one, it'll discharge.

308
00:24:10.180 --> 00:24:15.770
On this battlefield, it's impossible to
know when and where they'll strike.

309
00:24:15.770 --> 00:24:19.900
My contribution to defeating
that animal was minimal...

310
00:24:20.480 --> 00:24:23.570
since he fell victim to
the ordeal on his own.

311
00:24:30.370 --> 00:24:32.740
I take it you'll be
seeking revenge now?

312
00:24:33.280 --> 00:24:34.410
No.

313
00:24:35.290 --> 00:24:39.170
Fighting for revenge
isn't really my style.

314
00:24:40.250 --> 00:24:41.630
Oh?

315
00:24:42.250 --> 00:24:43.500
Is that so?

316
00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:44.380
But...

317
00:24:47.760 --> 00:24:50.510
I could make an exception.

318
00:25:03.020 --> 00:25:06.650
I'm sorry. Is this the
right place, Conis?

319
00:25:06.650 --> 00:25:09.150
They were going to meet
at this seashore, right?

320
00:25:09.150 --> 00:25:10.660
Yes, Father.

321
00:25:10.660 --> 00:25:12.870
Nami told me so.

322
00:25:13.370 --> 00:25:15.490
But what should we do?

323
00:25:15.490 --> 00:25:18.330
I didn't think we'd be the ones
looking after the ship.

324
00:25:19.080 --> 00:25:23.290
We must defend it at all
costs until they return!

325
00:25:23.290 --> 00:25:25.670
Shall we sound the horns
to scare off the enemy?

326
00:25:25.670 --> 00:25:27.590
Yes, Father!

327
00:25:27.590 --> 00:25:29.300
It'll be reassuring!

328
00:25:33.720 --> 00:25:35.720
This will do.

329
00:25:40.480 --> 00:25:43.610
Would you stand watch
over there, Suu?

330
00:25:49.820 --> 00:25:53.070
Okay! I'll do my best
to take care of you!

331
00:25:53.070 --> 00:25:54.820
Please hang on, both of you!

332
00:26:01.870 --> 00:26:04.540
Please, everyone... be safe...

333
00:26:04.540 --> 00:26:07.670
I'm sorry things are
like this on the sky island.

334
00:26:13.640 --> 00:26:15.300
Head to God's Shrine!

335
00:26:16.760 --> 00:26:19.970
Now is the time to take Enel's head!

336
00:26:22.190 --> 00:26:24.900
Don't let them get to God's Shrine!

337
00:26:25.310 --> 00:26:29.150
Climb up Giant Jack!

338
00:26:34.990 --> 00:26:38.540
Wyper! Don't use reject anymore!

339
00:26:39.620 --> 00:26:41.370
Warrior monks, retreat!

340
00:26:41.370 --> 00:26:43.250
Stop the Shaandians!

341
00:26:53.130 --> 00:26:55.340
Don't challenge Enel, Wyper!

342
00:27:01.310 --> 00:27:02.600
We can't...

343
00:27:03.140 --> 00:27:06.020
We can't defeat Enel! Ever!

344
00:27:26.920 --> 00:27:28.000
That's right.

345
00:27:28.790 --> 00:27:34.970
All of you, ascend to the Upper Ruins
and eliminate one another.

346
00:27:38.220 --> 00:27:40.890
There will be five survivors.

347
00:27:44.140 --> 00:27:48.900
God's prophecy is absolute.

348
00:27:58.490 --> 00:28:00.450
Enough, Wyper!

349
00:28:00.450 --> 00:28:01.910
I am–

350
00:28:01.910 --> 00:28:04.040
You're what?!

351
00:28:04.040 --> 00:28:06.250
You gonna say that
you're not my enemy?!

352
00:28:06.710 --> 00:28:11.290
To us, you and Enel
are the same, Gan Fall!

353
00:28:11.290 --> 00:28:14.170
So you refuse to listen, is that it?!

354
00:28:21.390 --> 00:28:22.430
You son of a bitch!

355
00:28:33.440 --> 00:28:37.450
My burn bazooka didn't work...
What's with those scales?!

356
00:28:42.330 --> 00:28:47.960
I... I can't take this cave anymore!

357
00:29:08.100 --> 00:29:10.350
What did you just...?

358
00:29:11.600 --> 00:29:14.440
This is why Blue Sea
people get on my nerves.

359
00:29:15.360 --> 00:29:18.990
This sword is also
made of iron cloud.

360
00:29:18.990 --> 00:29:20.860
In other words...

361
00:29:21.450 --> 00:29:27.450
iron cloud is added to the blade
by a dial built into the haft,

362
00:29:27.450 --> 00:29:29.790
so it won't allow anyone to escape!

363
00:29:33.960 --> 00:29:38.010
Were you able to understand that,
swordsman from the Blue Sea?

364
00:29:38.010 --> 00:29:40.090
Yeah, it's like a whip.

365
00:29:40.090 --> 00:29:44.720
I didn't know White-White Sea
warriors could be circus clowns too.

366
00:29:51.230 --> 00:29:52.230
Holy...

367
00:29:53.270 --> 00:29:54.770
Let's fight separately.

368
00:29:58.650 --> 00:30:03.490
It seems the Upper Ruins
are getting a little crowded.

369
00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:20.800
I didn't expect that even the Maaster of the Sky would be here...

370
00:30:20.800 --> 00:30:23.300
We will assist you, Master Ohm!

371
00:30:27.760 --> 00:30:28.970
You guys...!

372
00:30:30.480 --> 00:30:32.100
Looks like...

373
00:30:32.100 --> 00:30:34.850
Yeah, we're the only ones left.

374
00:30:34.850 --> 00:30:38.940
We'll help you reach Enel, Wyper!

375
00:30:45.030 --> 00:30:48.580
I got it! I'll just dig my way out!

376
00:30:56.040 --> 00:30:57.630
That giant snake...

377
00:31:02.220 --> 00:31:04.090
– ...is laughing!
– ...is laughing!

378
00:31:09.760 --> 00:31:11.310
Hold it!

379
00:31:13.060 --> 00:31:16.020
Go away!

380
00:31:16.020 --> 00:31:18.020
N-Nami?!

381
00:31:18.020 --> 00:31:18.900
Aisa!

382
00:31:18.900 --> 00:31:20.230
Young lady!

383
00:31:20.230 --> 00:31:21.980
Kill them!

384
00:31:38.920 --> 00:31:41.170
Aisa! What're you doing here?!

385
00:31:41.170 --> 00:31:43.710
Nami! Why're you here?!

386
00:31:45.090 --> 00:31:47.010
Zoro! Where is everyone?!

387
00:31:47.010 --> 00:31:48.180
Wyper!

388
00:31:48.180 --> 00:31:50.890
What are you Blue Sea
people plotting?!

389
00:31:51.350 --> 00:31:53.770
Aisa! Get away from that woman!

390
00:32:00.900 --> 00:32:02.280
That was close!

391
00:32:02.280 --> 00:32:05.490
Demon! You're a demon, Wyper!

392
00:32:05.860 --> 00:32:08.490
Why did you two come
to a place like this?!

393
00:32:08.490 --> 00:32:10.450
Why?!

394
00:32:10.450 --> 00:32:13.240
Because a huge...

395
00:32:13.910 --> 00:32:14.870
snake...

396
00:32:21.380 --> 00:32:23.000
That idiot...!

397
00:32:23.840 --> 00:32:24.960
Aisa!

398
00:32:38.270 --> 00:32:39.850
Wyper!

399
00:32:43.820 --> 00:32:47.320
You fools can't even
protect yourselves.

400
00:32:49.070 --> 00:32:51.410
Quit worrying about others!

401
00:32:52.410 --> 00:32:53.910
In the end...

402
00:32:53.910 --> 00:32:56.540
no one will survive!
